<br>
That being said, I would NEVER give up my horse for the world.  As a cleric, I do a whole lot of sitting and casting with VERY LITTLE movement or melee at all.  Therefore, having a horse of ANY speed is awesome for out door zones, especially KC and CoM.  This allows me to move around the party, cast, melee occassionaly, and meditate as if I was sitting down the whole time.  I can be sitting on my horse RIGHT NEXT TO A MOB and open my spell book to change out a spell.  The mob doesn't see me as sitting down, so I don't get added agro.<br>
<br>
From my experience, I would highly suggest a horse for any cleric, wizard, enchanter, or mage if you have 10kp sitting in your bank.  On the other hand, if you are not well equiped, spend the money on equipment BEFORE spending it on a horse.  The horse greatly helps, but the equipment is thx!<br>
